    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-09-28T12:36:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-09-28T12:36:00-05:00" n="1177"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1177">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.63/15.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Brazilian Minister to Mexico</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Brazilian Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico City</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-09-28T11:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 28, 1914, 11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>165. Government has issued a decree dated August 29 cancelling all mining titles
                    and declaring null all proceedings relative to the acquirement of mining claims
                    started during Huerta’s administration, in equity sixty days to make application
                    to mining agents to renew all previous procedure. Also that all usual payments
                    required by mining law in connection therewith be made again to the present
                    Government. Persons who have not complied with the above rulings before the end
                    of the sixty days will lose all their rights, the mining land being considered
                    thereafter as open to denouncement. As this term will expire November third and
                    considerable trouble will probably arise and severe loss ensue to many
                    foreigners please instruct me as to the course I should follow with regard to
                    American interests. As many Americans mine owners having large interests here
                    are now in the United States it might be well to give the above report wide
                    publication.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cardoso de Oliveira</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
